    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-09-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="708" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d708">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Partridge</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 18, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            very interesting despatch of the 26th August last, No. 11, with its
                            several accompaniments.</p>
                <p>The objections urged by the government of Honduras in regard to the
                            colonization of persons of African extraction in that republic are
                            regarded as conclusive by this government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James R. Partridge,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c. Honduras.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
